This paper is primarily concerned with the time complexity of distributed algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also deals with graph problems and their complexity, which is a topic in both Computer Science and Discrete Mathematics, and thus could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper presents new techniques for engineering LCL problems with specific time complexities, which could be of interest to researchers in Machine Learning and Information Theory, and thus could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
